=== Mental Health Support for Family

Depression and anxiety are common in both patients and family members. Warning signs requiring professional intervention:

    - *In patient*: Statements of hopelessness, suicidal ideation, complete disengagement, refusing all care
    - *In parents*: Inability to function, severe depression, relationship breakdown, child neglect
    - *In siblings*: Academic decline, behavioral changes, social withdrawal, expressed resentment toward ill sibling

Seek mental health support proactively rather than waiting for crisis. Family therapy addressing the systemic impact of chronic illness can benefit all members.

